{
  "stem": "8423.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They don't look at them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they beg for food or bread or whatever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they just are completely ignored.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they told us they were Polish people, because we didn't even know we were actually, because, you know, we arrived there.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were immersed in this atmosphere of smoke, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we were standing for our cell appel in the morning, there were such huge ashes falling and floating in the air, that they would land on us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course we had bare arms.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we tried to brush them off and it would just smear because it would be full of grease.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And it all came from the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we saw those crematoriums going night and day-- the red flames and the black smoke.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Night and day, they kept them going.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the trains kept coming.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I remember one particular train arriving.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We later found them-- found out that those people were coming from Vienna.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And some of the women got out of the train, and it was a very sunny day, and they open parasols.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They were very beautifully dressed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we found out later on that some of these were people who had converted and some where half-Christian or only had one Christian-- I mean, Jewish grandparent, or parents, and that they were very privileged.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But towards the end, because now this was the summer of 1944, they brought in all the ones that thought that, you know, by converting they would be treated specially.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Well they were for-- they were for a while, but then they brought them in, and I remember when I saw those parasols, I just absolutely couldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 29
    }
  ],
